member.summary:
A class which represents a "context" in NGINX config lingo. A context is what you might call a block - it has a list of directives and can potentially have blocks nested inside it too.
location / {
} ^ a location context "location /" is the directive of the above context. The list of directives (inside the brackets) in this example is empty.

